<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 1:44PM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Brief Funnel Clouds Possible With Showers This Afternoon...
At 140 PM, doppler radar indicated rain showers developing over
portions of northwest Illinois. These showers were slowly moving
southwest around 5 to 10 MPH.
These showers will be capable of producing funnel clouds through
the afternoon. Funnel clouds of this nature are short lived, and
rarely touch the ground. However, if you notice one approaching
the ground, move indoors to a place of safety.
The National Weather Service will continue to closely monitor the
situation. Please forward reports of funnel cloud sightings to
the nearest law enforcement agency for relay to the National
Weather Service.</description>
